The paper deals with computer vision techniques for analyzing first-person point-of-view videos, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses privacy concerns and social implications of wearable cameras, which could fall under the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. The paper also proposes a self-search technique that involves motion correlation, which could be related to multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses potential applications of the proposed technique for privacy filtering and target video retrieval, which could be related to the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category.
